---
/** Contrasts vanity metrics vs pipeline — who section. */
---
<div class="lp-viz lp-chart-bars" data-viz>
  <div class="lp-viz-head">
    <p class="lp-viz-kicker">What gets measured</p>
    <p class="lp-viz-title">Followers vs pipeline (typical failure mode)</p>
    <p class="lp-viz-note">
      If the work optimises for reach, you get charts that look good in a deck — not conversations that sound like referrals.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="lp-viz-bars" role="img" aria-label="Follower count bar long, qualified pipeline bar short before repositioning">
    <div class="lp-hbar">
      <span class="lp-hbar-label">Follower / activity scorecard</span>
      <div class="lp-hbar-track">
        <div class="lp-hbar-fill lp-hbar-fill--warn" style="--w: 88%"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="lp-hbar-cap">Vanity</span>
    </div>
    <div class="lp-hbar">
      <span class="lp-hbar-label">Qualified conversations tied to offer</span>
      <div class="lp-hbar-track">
        <div class="lp-hbar-fill lp-hbar-fill--accent" style="--w: 36%"></div>
      </div>
      <span class="lp-hbar-cap">Pipeline</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
